                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-07T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 7, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>114. Navy Department states that it is in radio communication with the battleship
                        <hi rend="italic">Latorre</hi> and that it and the two remaining mutinous
                    ships have agreed to surrender. Details of surrender not yet known.</p>
                <p>Repeated Lima.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
